{"title":"BMC Teammachine R brings Red Bull’s F1 Tech to the Road","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bmc-teammachine-r-2024/","date":1696665600000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2200\" height=\"1467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"bmc teammachine r racing road bike being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>After applying their aero know-how to the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2024-bmc-speedmachine/\">Speedmachine TT/triathlon bike last month</a>, BMC’s partnership with Red Bull Advanced Technologies (RBAT) yields a proper road bike. The all-new Teammachine R claims to perfectly balance weight, aerodynamics, and power transfer, and look good doing it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the TT bike, the collaboration does more than just focus on aerodynamics. Rider “feel” was high on the list, making it comfortable and giving the pilot more confidence so they can rider farther, faster, and longer.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"bmc teammachine r racing road bike being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also designed to be the ultimate race bike no matter the situation. Climbs, cobbles, and countless miles on the flats were all part of the test. The result is a bike that’s aero, but also reasonably light. Claimed frame weight is 910g (size 54) with a 345g fork, and complete bike weight of 7.0kg (15.43lbs).</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Novel aerodynamics</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of bmc teammachine r racing road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2-80x120.jpg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The now nearly standard full stealth cable routing is present, of course. A new Halo fork sets the legs very wide to more easily clear the front wheel’s turbulent air, keeping smoother air flowing over the frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6.jpg\"><img width=\"1620\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of bmc teammachine r racing road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6.jpg 1620w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6-297x220.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6-800x593.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6-120x89.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6-768x569.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-6-1536x1138.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other frontal areas were reduced with new tube shapes, and some tube profiles elongated. The result is less drag and improved performance in various crosswind angles, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5.jpg\"><img width=\"2200\" height=\"1467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5.jpg\" alt=\"bmc teammachine r racing road bike being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Integrated bottle cages further streamline airflow by making the bottle part of the overall aero profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9.jpg\"><img width=\"1440\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of bmc teammachine r racing road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9.jpg 1440w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-9-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Streamlined dropouts smooth the ends of the fork and rear triangle for marginal gains.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Power delivery and rider experience</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>BMC says the Teammachine R has the most efficient power transfer of any bike they’ve ever made. Some of that are the usual layup tricks, but the rest comes from a redesigned bottom bracket area…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11.jpg\"><img width=\"1440\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of bmc teammachine r racing road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11.jpg 1440w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-11-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>…and by tucking the rear wheel in as close as they could to the seat tube. The design also provides aerodynamic benefits, smoothing air flow onto the rear rim.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10.jpg\"><img width=\"1440\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10.jpg\" alt=\"integrated number plate holder on teammachine r\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10.jpg 1440w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-10-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Additional small touches like an add-on integrated number plate holder show the attention to detail they gave to every aspect of the bike</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Teammachine R Pricing &amp; Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7.jpg\"><img width=\"2058\" height=\"1257\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7.jpg\" alt=\"side view of bmc teammachine r racing road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7.jpg 2058w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-297x181.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-800x489.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-768x469.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-1536x938.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/BMC-Teammachine-R-racing-road-bike-7-2048x1251.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike comes in black/white, black/red, gray/red, and full black, and six sizes from 47 to 61.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Teammachine R 01 LTD (SRAM RED eTap AXS) – EUR 14,999 / USD / CHF</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Teammachine R 01 TWO (SHIMANO Dura Ace Di2) – EUR 13,999 / USD 14,499 / CHF 14,299</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Teammachine R 01 THREE (SRAM Force eTap AXS) – EUR 9,499 / USD 9,499 / CHF 9,699 </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Teammachine R 01 FOUR (SHIMANO Ultegra Di2) – EUR 8,999 / USD 9,199 / CHF 9,199</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Teammachine R 01 MOD (Frameset w/cockpit) – EUR 5,999 / USD / CHF</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.bmc-switzerland.com/teammachiner-redefine-racing\" target=\"_blank\">BMC-Switzerland.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bmc-teammachine-r-2024/\">BMC Teammachine R brings Red Bull’s F1 Tech to the Road</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"61f12ca119a5e3ade296760b0922659e9c15ddb67aacca00002ba5a42cdfa92a","category":"Cycling"}